139/* bn_expand acts the same as |bn_wexpand|, but takes a number of bits rather
140 * than a number of words. */
141BIGNUM *bn_expand(BIGNUM *bn, size_t bits);
142
143#if defined(OPENSSL_64_BIT)
144
145#if !defined(_MSC_VER)
146/* MSVC doesn't support two-word integers on 64-bit. */
147#define BN_ULLONG __uint128_t
148#endif
149
150#define BN_BITS2 64
151#define BN_BYTES 8
152#define BN_BITS4 32
153#define BN_MASK2 (0xffffffffffffffffUL)
154#define BN_MASK2l (0xffffffffUL)
155#define BN_MASK2h (0xffffffff00000000UL)
156#define BN_MASK2h1 (0xffffffff80000000UL)
157#define BN_TBIT (0x8000000000000000UL)
158#define BN_DEC_CONV (10000000000000000000UL)
159#define BN_DEC_NUM 19
160#define TOBN(hi, lo) ((BN_ULONG)hi << 32 | lo)
161
162#elif defined(OPENSSL_32_BIT)
163
164#define BN_ULLONG uint64_t
165#define BN_BITS2 32
166#define BN_BYTES 4
167#define BN_BITS4 16
168#define BN_MASK2 (0xffffffffUL)
169#define BN_MASK2l (0xffffUL)
170#define BN_MASK2h1 (0xffff8000UL)
171#define BN_MASK2h (0xffff0000UL)
172#define BN_TBIT (0x80000000UL)
173#define BN_DEC_CONV (1000000000UL)
174#define BN_DEC_NUM 9
175#define TOBN(hi, lo) lo, hi
176
177#else
178#error "Must define either OPENSSL_32_BIT or OPENSSL_64_BIT"
179#endif
180
181
182/* Pentium pro 16,16,16,32,64 */
183/* Alpha 16,16,16,16.64 */
184#define BN_MULL_SIZE_NORMAL (16) /* 32 */
185#define BN_MUL_RECURSIVE_SIZE_NORMAL (16) /* 32 less than */
186#define BN_SQR_RECURSIVE_SIZE_NORMAL (16) /* 32 */
187#define BN_MUL_LOW_RECURSIVE_SIZE_NORMAL (32) /* 32 */
188#define BN_MONT_CTX_SET_SIZE_WORD (64) /* 32 */

190#define STATIC_BIGNUM(x) \
191 { \
192 (BN_ULONG *)x, sizeof(x) / sizeof(BN_ULONG), \
193 sizeof(x) / sizeof(BN_ULONG), 0, BN_FLG_STATIC_DATA \
194 }
195
196#if defined(BN_ULLONG)
197#define Lw(t) (((BN_ULONG)(t))&BN_MASK2)
198#define Hw(t) (((BN_ULONG)((t)>>BN_BITS2))&BN_MASK2)
199#endif

201BN_ULONG bn_mul_add_words(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, int num, BN_ULONG w);
202BN_ULONG bn_mul_words(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, int num, BN_ULONG w);
203void bn_sqr_words(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, int num);
204BN_ULONG bn_div_words(BN_ULONG h, BN_ULONG l, BN_ULONG d);
205BN_ULONG bn_add_words(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, const BN_ULONG *bp,int num);
206BN_ULONG bn_sub_words(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, const BN_ULONG *bp,int num);

208void bn_mul_comba4(BN_ULONG *r, BN_ULONG *a, BN_ULONG *b);
209void bn_mul_comba8(BN_ULONG *r, BN_ULONG *a, BN_ULONG *b);
210void bn_sqr_comba8(BN_ULONG *r, const BN_ULONG *a);
211void bn_sqr_comba4(BN_ULONG *r, const BN_ULONG *a);
212
213/* bn_cmp_words returns a value less than, equal to or greater than zero if
214 * the, length |n|, array |a| is less than, equal to or greater than |b|. */
215int bn_cmp_words(const BN_ULONG *a, const BN_ULONG *b, int n);
216
217/* bn_cmp_words returns a value less than, equal to or greater than zero if the
218 * array |a| is less than, equal to or greater than |b|. The arrays can be of
219 * different lengths: |cl| gives the minimum of the two lengths and |dl| gives
220 * the length of |a| minus the length of |b|. */
221int bn_cmp_part_words(const BN_ULONG *a, const BN_ULONG *b, int cl, int dl);
222
223int bn_mul_mont(BN_ULONG *rp, const BN_ULONG *ap, const BN_ULONG *bp,
224 const BN_ULONG *np, const BN_ULONG *n0, int num);
225
226#if !defined(BN_ULLONG)
227
228#define LBITS(a) ((a) & BN_MASK2l)
229#define HBITS(a) (((a) >> BN_BITS4) & BN_MASK2l)
230#define L2HBITS(a) (((a) << BN_BITS4) & BN_MASK2)
231
232#define LLBITS(a) ((a) & BN_MASKl)
233#define LHBITS(a) (((a) >> BN_BITS2) & BN_MASKl)
234#define LL2HBITS(a) ((BN_ULLONG)((a) & BN_MASKl) << BN_BITS2)
235
236#define mul64(l, h, bl, bh) \
237 { \
238 BN_ULONG m, m1, lt, ht; \
239 \
240 lt = l; \
241 ht = h; \
242 m = (bh) * (lt); \
243 lt = (bl) * (lt); \
244 m1 = (bl) * (ht); \
245 ht = (bh) * (ht); \
246 m = (m + m1) & BN_MASK2; \
247 if (m < m1) \
248 ht += L2HBITS((BN_ULONG)1); \
249 ht += HBITS(m); \
250 m1 = L2HBITS(m); \
251 lt = (lt + m1) & BN_MASK2; \
252 if (lt < m1) \
253 ht++; \
254 (l) = lt; \
255 (h) = ht; \
256 }
257
258#endif /* !defined(BN_ULLONG) */
259
260#if !defined(OPENSSL_NO_ASM) && defined(OPENSSL_X86_64)
261# if defined(__GNUC__) && __GNUC__ >= 2
262# define BN_UMULT_HIGH(a,b) ({ \
263 register BN_ULONG ret,discard; \
264 __asm__ ("mulq %3" \
265 : "=a"(discard),"=d"(ret) \
266 : "a"(a), "g"(b) \
267 : "cc"); \
268 ret; })
269# define BN_UMULT_LOHI(low,high,a,b) \
270 __asm__ ("mulq %3" \
271 : "=a"(low),"=d"(high) \
272 : "a"(a),"g"(b) \
273 : "cc");
274# elif defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1400
275# define BN_UMULT_HIGH(a, b) __umulh((a), (b))
276# define BN_UMULT_LOHI(low, high, a, b) ((low) = _umul128((a), (b), &(high)))
277# endif
278#elif !defined(OPENSSL_NO_ASM) && defined(OPENSSL_AARCH64)
279# if defined(__GNUC__) && __GNUC__>=2
280# define BN_UMULT_HIGH(a,b) ({ \
281 register BN_ULONG ret; \
282 __asm__ ("umulh %0,%1,%2" \
283 : "=r"(ret) \
284 : "r"(a), "r"(b)); \
285 ret; })
286# endif
287#endif
288
289
290#if defined(__cplusplus)
291} /* extern C */
292#endif

294#endif /* OPENSSL_HEADER_BN_INTERNAL_H */
